content: The app is interesting. It allows easy and quick practice to keep progress on.
High level of usability, when to compared to competitors, the courses are great and accessible from mobile
it was free for mobile now tou need to pay , they didn't inform me before policy change so I could complete my courses , now they are locked in Middle of the progress.
I really enjoy the daily challenges that keep enforcing what you learned with online classes.
Dope. Nice for beginners who are "busy". Just do one exercise a day. Atomic habits
It's easy in the beginning but it gets challenging, you are able to do a course multiple times until you complete it. It gives advice on what to do when you didn't get it the first time. I love it
Awesome app to learn data topics on the go. Clean and smart UI. Informative and easy-to-follow content. Overall, it is a good and more mobile option aside from PC. Help protect the daily streak.

Excellent resource for those serious about learning data science. Builds your knowledge from the foundations and is consistently challenging enough to keep you interested, but not so hard that you're lost. Currently on a 150+ day streak with the premium plan, doing a chapter a day, when normally I'm not great with consistency and have a tendency to procrastinate. Haven't had any major issues with the app that a restart couldn't solve, and progress is now kept between the app and desktop site.

Great app to learn lessons in a more digestible manner than my current program class. I love the accesible videos with captions in various languages and there are examples that are explained WITH visuals! Would love to be able to be able to do 2 lessons a day instead of one (happened to me after a certain point in my progress) so if you are learning two languages then you can atleast do 1 lesson for each language.

Great adjustments made from the browser version for a high level of usability. Only thing that is lacking is to run single lines of code. Overall Datacamp is a great way to acquire data related skills. The app makes it possible to learn even on short breaks or on the way to work in the morning. Exactly what i was looking for!
Easy to follow lessons/explanations and options to practice coding when you progress far enough in. Definitely recommend to anyone trying to get into coding or other data-centric positions.

DataCamp is one of the fantastic app. I have come across. First their app is connected to their website. Unlike other apps, you can work in both places and your progress will be saved. Also, the user interface is without glitches. It's the best app for me.
" Your streak progress may not have been saved due to poor connectivity.." jeez. App is always disconnecting, even u r doing quiz. Jeeeeezzzz.

content: Data camp app gives the practical approach to learning in a simplified way.Safe-paced, hands-on, and insightful. I was amazed the progress I have made so far learning SQL, Python and R languages on the platform.
The best experience, Datacamp is structured to make you accountable and track your progress. It's been literally life saving, especially when you're overwhelmed by the complexities of coding.

One best platforms to learn data and machine learning related programming languages. This is one of the best choices I had made in my programming career. I just wished they could do better on the price. But compared to the rest their the most on point no easy BS around with you, not saying they don't easy you into it, just saying they don't cut have the info you need out just to make it easier or a better experience. if your for real want to be anything in the data field this is the place.

Data camp is a great and interactive app for learning. It is very engaging and easy to navigate. Learning is made fun and even addicting with the XPs gained and streaks given. It greatly facilitates the user's learning consistency. It is beginner friendly and has a whole lot of projects to practice on. I highly recommend this app! Great job data camp!
Bugs in the app are messing with my streak. Fix up

content: Great app for practically implementing high lvl projects. A degree of expected knowledge(find & learn), hold your hand a lot. Needs insight on what they provide or a link to reference language/function implemented. Let's you create a workspace. Would look better in dark mode. Certs, & group tabs are distracting. Groups tab is better socially if it was other ppls workspace to collaborate. We have no friends. Certs should be on the side with the competions sections. I recommend it though & like
It's a good starting point for learning data analytics and data science.

So well curated apt, concise, creatively put lessons . It ensures continuity in learning with its streak feature and learning data science is more fun than ever now . Thank you datacamp for providing this wonderfully developed platform.

Whether you learn fast or slow doesn't matter. DataCamp has got you covered and you can learn at your own pace. But there's more. It's designed to be engaging, highly interactive and so addicting that you'd never want to stop learning. The quizes are there to make sure you get the subtle differences. You'd want to keep pushing your boundaries and getting more points! And lastly, they keep improving and keep on adding more content so you get addicted to learning- which is good. LOL

Overall great courses. Not as easy to get an overview of your progress in a particular course or see where you are in the process as the web based version. Also, coding can be a bit wonky, sometimes putting in extra characters, or refusing to delete items, or deleting things out of order.
It's a very good starting point for beginners. I will recommend it to anyone looking to start a career in data science.

This is one of the best platforms to learn data science. Videos are straight to the point but very illustrative. So many practice exercises and projects to help one put to practice all the skills taught. I wish I have found this a long time ago.
Great app to progress your data skills, great UI &UX to learn. The points system makes it seems as you are playing a video game instead of traditional learning.
I started career track from desktop version but i cant find my progress from mobile app and continue learning same. Also if we use desktop version from mobile browser it is not user friendly

content: It's a very amazing app I love it so much very interactive but it has long hours before the next challenge

Concise, straight to the point and still adept at conveying information.I have a low attention span and the short videos with exercises after keep me enthralled.Love it😭❣️Thank you so much.Now, analyse the sentiments in my comment hehe.

Currently working through the Python Fundamentals Track (20+ modular course). It's more expensive than Udemy, but it's obvious why. Production is very good. The USP for me was the interactive python shell. You're introduced to a concept via a video, then apply it using real data. You can learn at your own speed and complete a daily challenge on what module you're currently studying. Hugo is good at keeping you motivated, funny guy.

content: Easy to digest due to the way everything has been broken down and laid out in a logical order. Each session comfortably roles into the next allowing for understanding each lesson easier as you progress through the syllabus.
I'm using the app for the simpler stuff I'm reviewing; and the desktop for the more challenging modules that require longer code and practice. Going good so far.
Very efficient and fast way of learning for beginners. The app is a useful resources and easy to navigate. The points and progress rating makes it all the more exciting.
The app is very interactive. You don't have to be a tech savvy to learn using the app. It also made learning fun and progressive for a newbie.
DataCamp app is great for a beginner level in coding. The daily challenge in app is a great way of a consistent learning.

I have a primium subscription. The content in the career path I was following using by desktop isn't available in the mobile app. I am really disappointed about this issue of not syncing the content. Hope you will address the issue soon.
Wow. This app is awesome. It is simple to use, the classes and exercises progresses smoothly. It is a nice educational tool. Thanks DataCamp for the opportunity to learn from you.

I've been studying Python and Tableau, as well as brushing up on my SQL. I've accessed this site on my laptop and my mobile device; both are comparably user-friendly. The in-browser coding window is the most bug-free of any site from which I've trained. I like the "hint" feature which gives a nudge in the right direction (with a small point penalty) without totally giving away the answer. Classes are well delivered well and the explanations are pretty clear.

I love the streak feature on this app because it helps me stay on track and I wouldn't want to break the streak. I also love that we get exercises immediately after the lesson, helps with brain power and keeps me engaged. Would recommend 💯.

discovered the Best Data Science Introduction, I could ever think of.. Loved the UI and the experience using the Data Camp app. As such, this certainly is one of the best learning sites, despite the heavy competition in the Industry.
Great experience thus far.. very educative and progressive.
Precise and straight to the point outline which easily and gradually built up my confidence in R and data science. Thanl you guys for this initiative
The application is incredible. I shown great progress on python, thanks very much.
I like the bite-size lessons and cloud-based programming. I do big projects on the computer, but use the app to squeeze in a little more learning during breaks at work, or in bed before sleeping.
App does not work properly and sound also break while video playing.

content: I love how engaging this app is, however, it's a bit annoying when you can't read all of the questions because it doesn't scroll all the way to the right. Perhaps put the 'questions' in a box like you do the examples of the code so you can scroll through them. Second peeve, is I wrote that exact code on one and it said I didn't. content: It's an amazing app that lets me learn an entire programming language with an expert-made course entirely for free. The videos are built-in for convenience, and the exercises are challenging enough for me to understand new concepts without being too difficult to be demotivating. Tl;dr It's a baller way to learn programming languages with daily practice.

I haven't had a good user experience with this app. You are only supposed to do the things which are expected by the app. For example, in the lesson about subsetting the lists in Python, they taught us about slicing and dicing in the same lesson. But you can't use that method in the early problems as you are supposed to take the long route of subsetting, instead of a better option. Overall it is a good app, but I didn't like this mentioned point.

Works less than half the time. When I'm not stuck physically in the code because the app does not allow me to move the cursor in the code, it gets stuck at running the code and keeps waiting for minutes, and then suddenly poof it works, but you've spent 5+ minutes on a super easy mini assignment. Super slow progress like this. Have had this issue on multiple android phone’s. I give up with their mobile app.
replyContent:

content: Compared to the web service, I do not understand the approach of the app. I can (even) not find the other courses I started, just the actual one. No chance to switch it on the mobile device. I also wanted to point out the "old" app, before the huge GUI revamp, was much better with regard to this point.

This is the best learning platform ever built. They make learning fun. The holistic approach used is ingenious. You practice the code as you are introduced to new topics using a coding environment built in so no need to worry about downloading the right shell or IDE. The learning is divided into bite size chunks and you are scored. I joined as part of a group from work and it encouraged constructive competition among us because there is a leader board. Please add more topics like hadoop...

The app is fine. Just missing one necessary feature. I understand that it's not possible to show most of the programming and data engineering courses here as in most of the cases, there is an code editor and terminal. But it would be nice if there were some kind of dashboard where we can see the progress we have made, in detail and in one short summary. Add this feature and I think you will get a lot of 5 stars.
I've learned so much through DataCamp. They pass so much across through short notes, videos and practice exercises, saves a lot of stress of lengthy videos not hitting the point quickly.

I appreciate the short lessons. It builds a confidence to learn the material. The interactive activities reinforces and challenge my comprehension of the information. I am excited 😊 to continue the learning experience. Thus far the value overall is the best I have had with a educational subscription service.

It's useful as a educational tool and they're very helpful, both the lectures and challenges. However the short blurbs as advertised are very easy to forget to do. With minimal reminders to return. Think of it like a gym membership, you can pay for it but that still means you have to go actually remember to work out

I know cheat sheets are available on the web version. Also, how about a Pandas for python tutorial?

replyContent: Hi, thank you for your feedback! For the more advanced DataCamp users we offer the practice mode (currently under the Practice tab at the bottom of the screen). There you can make extra exercises and deepen your understanding of some of the topics covered in the different tracks. We'll be adding more soon!

replyContent: Hi! Sorry for this problem. The only way to fix this is by reinstalling the app. This problem was caused by an update in the app, that we've now rolled back. We're really sorry for the inconvenience, and hope you'll enjoy the app again after this fix.

replyContent: Hi Siva Taru Pikkili! Sorry to disappoint you. At the moment only the intro courses are available. We're working very hard to port the other courses into a mobile format as well, but it isn't something we can do within just one month. This is just a first version of the app. More courses will follow soon. But now people can already start learning.

replyContent:
Hi! Thank you for your review. We are sorry to hear that you don't have the best experience. 

We are working hard on bringing more courses to the app, but as we want to make them to be as good on mobile as they are on web, it takes a lot of time. 

What should we improve to make the app worth 5 stars?

content: good start! but at the moment incomplete compared to web courses. want to seamlessly switch between desktop and mobile w.o. loosing progress or starting separate courses. keep up the good work! really enjoying your content!
replyContent: Thank you for the rating! We are working hard to implement these suggestions :) If you have any more feedback, we are always interested! You can also let us know via mobile@datacamp.com.
